sec.p:
The probability of an infectious contact between cases i and j, πij(v,w), is informed by the contact information collected during the outbreak, such that:


πij(v, w) = 1, if case j is the only possible infector of case i;

πij(v, w) = 1/m, if case j is one of m contacts and a possible infector of case i;

πij(v, w) = 1/(i − 1), if there are no contacts for case i and it is not an index case.
